item.description:
tl;dr if you care about maximum compatibility with different versions of GNU Make, don&rsquo;t use .SHELLARGS just put all your args in-line in the SHELL variable, and make sure to always always use -c as your last argument.
E.g. for bash in &ldquo;strict mode&rdquo;
SHELL := /usr/bin/env bash -euo pipefail -c  But why? I really care about the out of the box development experience on projects I maintain. For me, this currently means ensuring that you can at least build and run tests on vanilla macOS and LTS GNU/Linux distros, without having to upgrade standard tools like, for example, make.
